title: McGowan's Madison Avenue Axiom
quote: If an item is advertised as "under $50", you can bet it's not $19.95.

title: Van Roy's Law
quote: An unbreakable toy is useful for breaking other toy
How long a minute is depends on which side of the bathroom door you're on.
Don't worry over what other people are thinking about you.  They're too busy worrying over what you are thinking about them.

title: Ducharm's Axiom
quote: If you view your problem closely enough you will recognize yourself as part of the problem

title: A Law of Computer Programming
quote: Make it possible for programmers to write in English and you will find the programmers cannot write in English.

title: Turnaucka's Law
quote: The attention span of a computer is only as long as its electrical cord
The past always looks better than it was.  It's only pleasant because it isn't here
author: Finley Peter Dunne (Mr. Dooley)
